==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Abidance
<hw>A*bid"ance</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of
abiding; abode; continuance; compliance (<xex>with</xex>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Christians had no longer <qex>abidance</qex> in the holy hill
of Palestine.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A judicious <qex>abidance</qex> by rules.</q>
<rj><qau>Helps.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abide</ent>⟦br⟧
